{{en-noun|sg=[[friendly]] [[suit]]}}

# {{law}}: Where [[two]] [[subsidiaries]] of the same [[parent company]] accidently sue each other, not realising that they have the same owner.  An analogy is "friendly fire", where a person accidentally shoots someone on his or her own side.
# {{law}}: Where a person sues another person (friend) purely to settle a point of (unsettled) law.